<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="270" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="19" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,799,825]" pageId="19" pageNumber="270">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2022" box="[468,635,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Nigripeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octa">
<emphasis box="[468,635,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="270">Nigripeza octa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was applied to this species because it has long carried the manuscript name &quot;species 8&quot;.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="270" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="19" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,870,896]" pageId="19" pageNumber="270">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2022" box="[345,510,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Nigripeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octa">
<emphasis box="[345,510,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="270">Nigripeza octa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only Central American species in this otherwise South American genus. The 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,907,933]" pageId="19" pageNumber="270">holotype</typeStatus>
shows unusual apparent asymmetry in the number of dorsocentral bristles, a character that is usually stable and symmetrical. A specimen of this species (labelled TAE089) was treated under the manuscript name 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="270">
<taxonomicName box="[1316,1436,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Grallipeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Grallipeza</taxonomicName>
&quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2022" box="[161,213,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Nigripeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octa">octa</taxonomicName>
&quot;
</emphasis>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Jackson, M. &amp; Marshall, S. &amp; Skevington, J." box="[260,473,978,1005]" pageId="19" pageNumber="270" pagination="411 - 430" refId="ref12305" refString="Jackson, M., Marshall, S. &amp; Skevington, J. (2015) Molecular phylogeny of the Taeniapterini (Diptera: Micropezidae) using nuclear and mitochondrial DNA, with a reclassification of the genus Taeniaptera Macquart. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, 46 (5), 411 - 430. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 1876312 X- 45032125" type="journal article" year="2015">
Jackson 
<emphasis box="[356,406,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="270">et al</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
. It was the only species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2022" box="[779,889,979,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Nigripeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[779,889,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="270">Nigripeza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2022" box="[928,1031,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Amapeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[928,1031,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="270">Amapeza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
included in that paper, in which the Majority Rule Consensus cladogram recovered it as sister to a clade including 
<taxonomicName authority="Cresson" authorityName="Cresson" authorityYear="1926" box="[1031,1300,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1031,1204,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="270">Hoplocheiloma</emphasis>
Cresson
</taxonomicName>
and the one species of 
<emphasis box="[269,418,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="270">
<taxonomicName box="[269,389,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Grallipeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Grallipeza</taxonomicName>
ss
</emphasis>
included in the paper.
</paragraph>
